cs.DC, cs.MM, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.CY

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper discusses the design and implementation of a web-based multimedia conferencing system, which involves distributed computing and communication among multiple users. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper focuses on improving the quality of multimedia services in the context of SOA, specifically in multimedia conferencing. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the use of Service Oriented Communication in the design of the multimedia conferencing system, which involves networking and internet architecture. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper involves the use of a hybrid orchestration of web and communication services, which can be seen as a social network of services. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper may also fall under this category as it discusses the impact of QoS violations on user satisfaction and proposes a solution to address the problem.
